<subSubSection id="C31E6567FFC1F62F8C643C60F9D8F689" pageId="5" pageNumber="63" type="conservation">
<paragraph id="8BBB36ECFFC1F62F8C643C60F9D8F689" blockId="5.[1400,2612,829,2403]" pageId="5" pageNumber="63">
<emphasis id="B970EAFEFFC1F62F8C643C60F970F706" bold="true" box="[1402,1749,2172,2205]" pageId="5" pageNumber="63">Status and Conservation.</emphasis>
Classified as Vulnerable on The IUCN Red List. The Javan Tailless Fruit Bat is uncommon, and population trend is decreasing, chiefly due to habitat loss from logging and mining activities. Population is divided among three islands, but these are adjacent.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
